Section 1:
Act 376 of the Regular Session
1 State of Arkansas As Engrossed: H2/27/25 H3/3/25 H3/5/25
A Bill
2 95th General Assembly
3 Regular Session, 2025 HOUSE BILL 1575
4
5 By: Representatives Lundstrum, Unger
6 By: Senator J. Bryant
7
For An Act To Be Entitled
8
9 AN ACT TO PROHIBIT A PERSON THAT IS EMPLOYED OR HAS A
10 DIRECT OR INDIRECT FINANCIAL INTEREST IN A FIRM,
11 BUSINESS, OR ORGANIZATION THAT OWNS, OPERATES,
12 REPRESENTS, OR APPLIES FOR A SOLID WASTE LICENSE OR
13 PERMIT FROM SERVING AS A MEMBER ON CERTAIN
14 COMMISSIONS AND BOARDS; AND FOR OTHER PURPOSES.
15
16
Subtitle
17
18 TO PROHIBIT A PERSON THAT IS EMPLOYED OR
19 HAS A DIRECT OR INDIRECT INTEREST IN AN
20 ORGANIZATION THAT OWNS, OPERATES,
21 REPRESENTS, OR APPLIES FOR A SOLID WASTE
22 LICENSE OR PERMIT FROM SERVING AS A
23 MEMBER ON CERTAIN BOARDS.
24
25 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF ARKANSAS:
26
27 SECTION 1. Arkansas Code ยง 8-4-104, concerning the membership of the
28 Arkansas Pollution Control and Ecology Commission, is amended to add an
29 additional subsection to read as follows:
30 (h) A person shall not serve as a member of the Arkansas Pollution
31 Control and Ecology Commission if he or she is employed by a firm, business,
32 or organization that owns, operates, represents, or applies for a solid waste
33 license or permit or in which that person has a direct or indirect financial
34 interest.
35
36 SECTION 2. Arkansas Code ยง 8-6-703, concerning the creation of
*JMB291*
03-05-2025 10:58:45 JMB291
As Engrossed: H2/27/25 H3/3/25 H3/5/25 HB1575
1 regional solid waste planning districts and boards, is amended to add an
2 additional subsection to read as follows:
3 (d)(1) A person shall not serve as a member of the board if he or she
4 is employed by a firm, business, or organization that owns, operates,
5 represents, or applies for a solid waste license or permit or in which that
6 person has a direct or indirect financial interest.
7 (2) Subdivision (d)(1) of this section does not apply to an
8 elected official or an employee of a city or county that is required to
9 represent a city or county on a regional solid waste planning district or
10 board under subsection (b) of this section.
